            N("Review verdict", "The supplied DBML is a useful first draft but is not production-ready. It mixes mutable balances with history, keys PO lines by version, models BOM changes as intervals rather than full snapshots, and lacks reproducible policy snapshots, exact-once inventory posting, signer identity, sessions, outbox delivery, and tamper-evident audit chaining. This ERD corrects those structural gaps."),
            N("PostgreSQL 16+ conventions", "Use uuid identifiers (prefer UUIDv7 generated by the application or an approved extension), timestamptz in UTC for instants, date for business dates, numeric(20,4) for quantities/prices, char(n) only for confirmed fixed-length codes, jsonb only for immutable snapshots/payloads, and object storage for file bytes. Enable RLS by project and revoke UPDATE/DELETE on append-only tables."),
            N("Stable facts vs projections", "PO versions, BOM revisions, launch items, partial-production events, inventory postings, status history, confirmations, signatures, price/cost periods, and audit events are immutable facts. Current PO progress, stock balances, actual sales, revenue, threshold state, and dashboards are views/materialized projections. Never repair history by overwriting a fact; append a correction/reversal."),
            N("Major reconciliations", "Stable purchase_order_items survive every PO version and join typed launch, production, and confirmed-delivery facts. All 20 extracted fields retain validation detail; immutable PO rows snapshot customer/contact/FGPN/development labels. BOM revisions are complete xlsx snapshots. Simulations snapshot multi-PO progress plus warehouse/WIP/transit/planned stock and dated future arrivals."),
            N("Inventory correctness", "Locations belong to explicit stock pools and project_stock_pools defines shared versus project-scoped access. Every stock-changing command creates one inventory_event and immutable signed postings atomically. UNIQUE source/idempotency keys plus payload_hash give exactly-once acceptance. Balance views are projections, never manually edited."),
            N("Documents and audit", "documents stores immutable SHA-256 metadata, an external KMS key/version reference, and retention/legal-hold controls. Domain rows hold normal FKs to documents; signatures retain typed signer identity and display snapshot. audit_events is append-only and hash-chained, and outbox_events commits with the business fact."),
            N("Open points OP-01 to OP-04", "OP-01 FGPN length remains configurable; no false length CHECK is imposed until a real example is approved. OP-02/03/04 role scope remains policy data through permissions, role_permissions, one temporal active user role, temporal project assignments, and server-side RLS. Plant Manager stays read-only, Launch Manager writes assigned projects, and Warehouse Personnel remains least-privilege pending confirmation."),
            N("Open points OP-05 to OP-09", "OP-05 status moves are unique from/to rows with allowed roles in po_status_transition_roles; backward moves require a reason. OP-06 priority/tie-break rules are immutable simulation policy versions. OP-07 confirmation requires explicit evidence, with accepted form configurable. OP-08 delivery methods are typed master data. OP-09 safety coefficient defaults to 2 only as versioned policy data."),
            N("Open points OP-10 to OP-13", "OP-10 signed warehouse receipt validation stores validator and time before the inventory event is posted. OP-11 invoice requirement is a system setting/policy rule. OP-12 future-simulation drafts are persisted as documents. OP-13 code TTL is a setting seeded to 48 hours until business sign-off; codes are hashed, unique, expiring, and single-use."),
            N("Key data rules", "PO number: char(10), length 10. PO part number: char(7). Color code: char(4). PO level: varchar(6). Unit price and quantities: numeric(20,4), non-negative/positive as appropriate. Descriptions: varchar(50). Material part number: varchar(10). PO/BOM/CutMan/signed/invoice file formats are enforced by domain checks plus content sniffing; CutMan SQL is parsed as data and never executed."),
            N("Concurrency and lifecycle", "Mutable aggregates carry row_version bigint for optimistic locking. user_sessions implements the configurable 60-minute inactivity timeout and revocation. Deactivate reference/users instead of deleting. Deferred constraint triggers enforce cross-table rules such as same-project references, final launch meeting minutes, confirmation before Delivered, and delivered quantity not exceeding the current ordered quantity."),
            N("Legend", "Blue IAM/reference | Orange PO | Purple BOM/simulation | Green inventory | Teal deliveries | Gold finance | Red audit | Grey views/projections | Yellow invariants/open decisions. PK/FK/UQ/CK/IX/GEN mean primary key, foreign key, unique, check, index, and generated value."),
